image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

commentTextItems.html: flicked to square leg to end of the innings.

commentPostTextItems.html: And that brings to an end this quite interesting day of cricket, some suprises, some dissapointing, some pleasant. Zimbabwe really put in  a great effort and the two men that really steered this innings, Taibu and Matsikenyeri really have set the red lights burning bright in the Proteas camp and hopefully they will answer to these danger signs. The Proteas might have won this game by 45 runs, but it is the Zimbabweans who will go home the happier team tonight. Please join us again on Tuesday for the 2nd and last ODI with South Africa taking on Zimbabwe live from Centurion, South Africa.

commentTextItems.html: Worked off his hips again to get another couple.
real sloppy from South Africa. Really no great effort here this afternoon from the Proteas.
what an innings from the little man. Worked off his thigh, gets an easy single. A great innings from the seasoned cricketer.
defended off the frontfoot and not taking any chances with a single.
short of a length and straight, flicked over the square leg fielder and goes all the way.
driven out to third man. Could've gotten two if they had ran hard, but Taibu choosing to keep the strike being 7 shy of his century.

commentPostTextItems.html: Albie morkel to bowl the final over of this match.

commentTextItems.html: driven out to cover. Miss-field,but no run taken.
swing and miss from Cremer. Steyn's pace just too much.
worked down to third man with a great little late cut.
rotates the strike by running the ball down to third man.
driven to cover for an easy single as all the fielder are on the edge of the ring.

headshotImage.caption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mark Vermeulen c Amla b Tsotsobe 8 (18b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: finally Tsotsobe is rewarded with a wicket. Slower ball luring Vermeulen to go over the top and is miss-timed straight to Amla at mid-off.

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha lbw b McLaren 21 (30b 3x4 0x6 46m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: and McLaren gets his first ODI wicket on just his 3rd delivery. A bit high and moving towards the leg-side, but umpire Rudi Koertzen lifts the finger.

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Mark Boucher player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Boucher player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c †Boucher b McLaren 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: edged and well taken by Boucher, diving to his right.

headshotImage.caption: Mark Boucher player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mark Boucher player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c †Boucher b Steyn 11 (38b 0x4 0x6 47m) SR: 28.94

dismissalComment.html: another good take by Boucher. Steyn luring him into the drive, gets the edge and Boucher makes no mistake.

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura b Steyn 4 (4b 1x4 0x6 5m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: another good take by Boucher. Steyn luring him into the drive, gets the edge and Boucher makes no mistake.

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b McLaren 86 (87b 8x4 1x6 114m) SR: 98.85

dismissalComment.html: finally the 188run-partnership is broken with an in-swinging yorker. Matsikenyeri departs for 86 runs. Excellent knock comes to an end.

milestones.description: Tatenda Taibu and Stuart's 188-run partnership is ZIM's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 114 between Stuart and Chigumbura
